1
00:00:59,976 --> 00:01:03,646
Come on. How could this serve as evidence?

2
00:01:03,730 --> 00:01:06,941
I tapped the back of her shoulder in 2016?

3
00:01:07,025 --> 00:01:09,778
Bringing it up now
is just totally ridiculous.

4
00:01:09,861 --> 00:01:11,863
-But you probably did--
-You did it, though.

5
00:01:14,616 --> 00:01:18,578
Even if I really did tap her
on the back of her shoulder,

6
00:01:18,661 --> 00:01:21,581
what about the statute of limitations?
It happened in 2016.

7
00:01:21,664 --> 00:01:24,501
There can't be
a three-year statute of limitations on it.

8
00:01:25,210 --> 00:01:28,546
The thing is, that shoulder incident

9
00:01:29,089 --> 00:01:31,549
isn't the only case
described in this ledger.

10
00:01:33,885 --> 00:01:35,136
My eyes are so dry.

11
00:01:36,179 --> 00:01:38,515
What? Did you actually cry?

12
00:01:38,598 --> 00:01:41,309
-Jeez, why would I cry?
-This is ridiculous.

13
00:01:41,392 --> 00:01:44,312
-Goodness.
-All right. I'll tell you what I think.

14
00:01:44,938 --> 00:01:49,359
All the incidents are described
in great detail in this ledger.

15
00:01:49,776 --> 00:01:54,280
And what you did is utterly disgusting.

16
00:01:54,823 --> 00:01:58,034
I'd say this can serve
as irrefutable evidence.

17
00:01:58,118 --> 00:02:00,036
That is my legal conclusion.

18
00:02:00,120 --> 00:02:01,955
Did you go to law school?

19
00:02:02,914 --> 00:02:05,792
Honey, say something.
These clueless people think

20
00:02:05,875 --> 00:02:08,294
they can say
whatever they want and call it the law.

21
00:02:21,307 --> 00:02:25,061
So? Do you really plan to press charges
against my husband?

22
00:02:29,691 --> 00:02:31,151
Yes, that is my plan.

23
00:02:32,026 --> 00:02:33,403
But he's your landlord.

24
00:02:34,154 --> 00:02:36,573
He has a lot of money,
and he's well-connected.

25
00:02:41,953 --> 00:02:43,329
Still, I want to do it.

26
00:02:43,913 --> 00:02:45,623
You know I'm a lawyer, right?

27
00:02:46,833 --> 00:02:48,543
It won't be an easy fight.

28
00:02:48,751 --> 00:02:52,547
My wife went to Seoul National University
Law School.

29
00:02:52,755 --> 00:02:55,842
Her old classmates are now lawyers
at top-notch law firms.

30
00:02:56,551 --> 00:02:58,344
I'm that competent.

31
00:03:02,348 --> 00:03:03,433
So...

32
00:03:16,821 --> 00:03:18,323
call me if you need legal advice.

33
00:03:18,406 --> 00:03:20,074
HONG JA-YEONG LAW OFFICE

34
00:03:22,493 --> 00:03:24,662
You don't need to pay me.

35
00:03:38,009 --> 00:03:39,886
Hong Ja-yeong!

36
00:03:53,358 --> 00:03:55,360
Why do you guys keep following me?

37
00:03:56,069 --> 00:03:58,529
Can't you just say something?

38
00:03:58,613 --> 00:03:59,614
Say what?

39
00:03:59,781 --> 00:04:02,200
Let's split up and go our own ways.

40
00:04:02,742 --> 00:04:04,744
Gosh, seriously. This is so unlike you.

41
00:04:04,827 --> 00:04:07,538
You're not even smacking me.
Just slap me on the back!

42
00:04:07,622 --> 00:04:08,915
You're scaring me.

43
00:04:10,166 --> 00:04:12,293
I have a headache. I should head in.

44
00:04:13,211 --> 00:04:16,589
Dongbaek.
Why are you following her inside?

45
00:04:17,382 --> 00:04:18,967
Don't come inside.

46
00:04:19,384 --> 00:04:20,385
Dongbaek.

47
00:04:22,553 --> 00:04:23,972
My mom can hit you.

48
00:04:24,514 --> 00:04:26,266
Stop talking nonsense. Just get going.

49
00:04:28,518 --> 00:04:30,520
BAEKDU GRANDMA MARINATED CRAB

50
00:04:32,522 --> 00:04:34,440
Gosh, this is bad.

51
00:04:36,359 --> 00:04:38,236
I must've been out of my mind.

52
00:04:38,987 --> 00:04:40,863
What was I thinking?

53
00:04:41,447 --> 00:04:44,158
Gosh, I'm so mean.

54
00:04:44,575 --> 00:04:47,495
I'm such a traitor. What a sneaky bitch.

55
00:04:48,538 --> 00:04:50,290
You don't have the guts to be a bitch.

56
00:04:54,836 --> 00:04:57,547
I tried so hard to act

57
00:04:58,089 --> 00:05:00,466
all haughty and tough.

58
00:05:02,593 --> 00:05:04,012
But the thing is, Ms. Kwak...

59
00:05:06,514 --> 00:05:07,890
I guess...

60
00:05:13,187 --> 00:05:14,731
I missed having someone around.

61
00:05:20,695 --> 00:05:23,656
I guess I missed having someone
who cares and worries about me.

62
00:05:25,491 --> 00:05:27,577
I realized that one person
who worries about me

63
00:05:29,579 --> 00:05:32,123
can change my whole world.

64
00:05:34,375 --> 00:05:36,127
What should I do?

65
00:05:37,086 --> 00:05:39,213
And what would you do?

66
00:05:41,632 --> 00:05:43,593
BAEKDU GRANDMA MARINATED CRAB

67
00:05:53,353 --> 00:05:55,480
Parents can never win
against their children,

68
00:05:55,688 --> 00:05:57,565
so what can I do?

69
00:05:58,775 --> 00:06:02,570
I'd beat him up if he were 15.

70
00:06:03,279 --> 00:06:06,574
He's acting like he's 15
when he's over 30 now.

71
00:06:06,741 --> 00:06:08,409
How could I stop him?

72
00:06:10,703 --> 00:06:14,415
I can only rely on time.

73
00:06:15,083 --> 00:06:17,001
If it's just a shower, it will stop.

74
00:06:20,004 --> 00:06:20,838
Right.

75
00:06:23,925 --> 00:06:27,178
Do you think I'm heartless
for saying things like this?

76
00:06:28,846 --> 00:06:29,847
No.

77
00:06:33,017 --> 00:06:36,229
You're so calm and collected,
which is making me feel even worse.

78
00:06:38,272 --> 00:06:42,026
A fire that burns quickly
also fizzles out quickly.

79
00:06:42,735 --> 00:06:45,780
And men are a lot more fickle-minded
than women are.

80
00:06:47,407 --> 00:06:50,493
So don't just fall for anyone
when they say

81
00:06:50,576 --> 00:06:52,328
they'll give you their everything.

82
00:06:52,912 --> 00:06:55,081
You should take time
and really observe him.

83
00:06:57,333 --> 00:07:00,086
If you still want to be with him
even after watching him

84
00:07:01,212 --> 00:07:02,964
for a long time...

85
00:07:12,557 --> 00:07:14,559
We can talk about it again
when that happens.

86
00:07:24,861 --> 00:07:25,903
If...

87
00:07:29,449 --> 00:07:32,034
I'm sure I want to be with him
even after watching him,

88
00:07:33,286 --> 00:07:36,122
will you approve of me?

89
00:07:42,753 --> 00:07:43,838
Dongbaek.

90
00:07:44,505 --> 00:07:47,091
I'm sure you can understand
because you're raising Pil-gu.

91
00:07:47,884 --> 00:07:50,428
My heart broke even when
he put his feet in mud

92
00:07:50,511 --> 00:07:52,430
because he is my dear son.

93
00:07:52,930 --> 00:07:55,308
Knowing how hard it is
to raise someone else's child,

94
00:07:55,475 --> 00:07:57,351
how could I tell him to choose that path?

95
00:08:05,026 --> 00:08:05,860
Right.

96
00:08:15,953 --> 00:08:16,954
Dongbaek.

97
00:08:18,289 --> 00:08:19,999
Gosh, I told you to just go.

98
00:08:20,458 --> 00:08:21,542
Dongbaek.

99
00:08:23,878 --> 00:08:26,964
Well, do you want to go
have some dumplings with me?

100
00:08:28,299 --> 00:08:31,302
As they say, you can't do anything
if you don't eat.

101
00:08:32,303 --> 00:08:35,515
Your heart and intestines
are only a handspan apart,

102
00:08:35,598 --> 00:08:39,018
so you need to fill up your stomach
when you're upset.

103
00:08:39,101 --> 00:08:43,272
That fills you up
emotionally as well, and...

104
00:08:47,818 --> 00:08:50,404
Okay, let's go.
Let's go for some dumplings.

105
00:08:51,280 --> 00:08:52,240
-What?
-Let's go.

106
00:08:52,323 --> 00:08:53,699
We're going? Really?

107
00:09:09,048 --> 00:09:11,884
I have to admit that
I do care a bit about you.

108
00:09:12,260 --> 00:09:15,763
Even earlier, I went all crazy
because I was worried

109
00:09:15,846 --> 00:09:17,640
that you might end up in jail.

110
00:09:19,058 --> 00:09:21,769
I've been crazy about you
for a long time now.

111
00:09:23,354 --> 00:09:24,730
Even at the police station,

112
00:09:26,440 --> 00:09:29,402
I could only see you.
I couldn't even see Ms. Kwak.

113
00:09:29,485 --> 00:09:30,611
Like a disloyal bitch.

114
00:09:31,404 --> 00:09:32,905
I really shouldn't be like this.

115
00:09:34,156 --> 00:09:36,158
Am I bewitched by something?

116
00:09:37,702 --> 00:09:40,413
Dongbaek, I've been bewitched by you
for a long time.

117
00:09:42,373 --> 00:09:47,211
But when I see Ms. Kwak,
I feel so guilty and bad.

118
00:09:49,797 --> 00:09:54,218
And now that I'm sitting here with you
to have dumplings,

119
00:09:54,885 --> 00:09:56,345
I feel...

120
00:09:59,765 --> 00:10:00,891
You feel happy, right?

121
00:10:03,352 --> 00:10:07,023
You actually feel good inside, don't you?

122
00:10:11,485 --> 00:10:16,115
Well, then perhaps we should...

123
00:10:18,034 --> 00:10:19,327
I'm not going to date you.

124
00:10:20,620 --> 00:10:21,454
What?

125
00:10:24,707 --> 00:10:27,126
Now that it's all out in the open,

126
00:10:28,794 --> 00:10:33,716
let me tell you exactly what's going on
so that you don't overreact.

127
00:10:35,468 --> 00:10:37,386
I do care about you,

128
00:10:37,887 --> 00:10:40,431
but it's not like I'm so crazy about you
that I'll ignore

129
00:10:40,514 --> 00:10:43,309
what Ms. Kwak, Pil-gu,
and everyone else thinks.

130
00:10:43,601 --> 00:10:46,062
And I don't want things
to get that messy anyway.

131
00:10:46,979 --> 00:10:49,398
Why is that "messy"?

132
00:10:49,690 --> 00:10:51,150
Love is like fire.

133
00:10:51,233 --> 00:10:52,902
No, I don't want that.

134
00:10:54,695 --> 00:10:55,529
Well...

135
00:10:57,406 --> 00:10:59,408
As you know,
I've been in that kind of love.

136
00:11:01,827 --> 00:11:02,745
And I lost.

137
00:11:07,541 --> 00:11:10,127
I'm not young,

138
00:11:10,211 --> 00:11:12,213
and I'm not alone.

139
00:11:13,422 --> 00:11:14,590
I have to earn money too.

140
00:11:15,966 --> 00:11:19,804
I can't shove everything aside
and get all lovey-dovey.

141
00:11:20,096 --> 00:11:24,058
Find someone else if you want
some kind of passionate relationship.

142
00:11:24,141 --> 00:11:25,601
I'm not doing it.

143
00:11:28,729 --> 00:11:30,856
You're pushing me away again.

144
00:11:33,442 --> 00:11:36,862
Let's drop it. Why don't we just eat

145
00:11:37,822 --> 00:11:38,864
these dumplings?

146
00:11:50,334 --> 00:11:51,377
Yong-sik.

147
00:11:53,045 --> 00:11:56,215
Steam is all you need to cook dumplings,
you know.

148
00:11:56,882 --> 00:11:59,301
You don't have to boil them to cook them.

149
00:11:59,885 --> 00:12:01,095
Right.

150
00:12:05,641 --> 00:12:07,810
Forget fire.

151
00:12:08,269 --> 00:12:09,270
Why don't we

152
00:12:10,396 --> 00:12:13,315
just take it slow and be warm together?

153
00:12:20,281 --> 00:12:22,992
You can love like fire,
but it's all over when you break up.

154
00:12:24,702 --> 00:12:26,287
I've had to say goodbye to my mom

155
00:12:27,955 --> 00:12:29,665
as well as to that guy.

156
00:12:30,875 --> 00:12:34,253
If I have to go through that again...
Gosh, I can't do it.

157
00:12:34,670 --> 00:12:36,422
Then I'll really be knocked out.

158
00:12:44,722 --> 00:12:47,349
So, you're saying...

159
00:12:48,976 --> 00:12:51,145
I mean, you want us

160
00:12:51,353 --> 00:12:56,984
to do something together, right?

161
00:12:57,651 --> 00:12:58,652
Yes.

162
00:13:00,029 --> 00:13:01,071
Let's just...

163
00:13:04,950 --> 00:13:05,868
Well...

164
00:13:07,244 --> 00:13:09,914
Let's see how things go.

165
00:13:21,801 --> 00:13:22,885
I want to be warm

166
00:13:24,094 --> 00:13:25,221
for a long time.

167
00:13:44,698 --> 00:13:46,617
I'll take back what I said if you cry.

168
00:13:49,036 --> 00:13:49,870
Okay.

169
00:13:53,040 --> 00:13:53,999
Thanks.

170
00:13:55,876 --> 00:13:58,879
KAESONG DUMPLINGS

171
00:13:59,839 --> 00:14:02,758
So your priority is being Pil-gu's mom

172
00:14:03,259 --> 00:14:04,802
and the owner of Camellia.

173
00:14:05,344 --> 00:14:07,888
And after that, you're...

174
00:14:09,223 --> 00:14:12,059
So you should also prioritize
being a good son to Ms. Kwak

175
00:14:12,142 --> 00:14:14,979
and a good police officer
for the community of Ongsan.

176
00:14:15,062 --> 00:14:18,774
After you do all that,
we can hang out and see how things go.

177
00:14:19,608 --> 00:14:21,861
And please go and check
on Yeong-sim's dog.

178
00:14:21,944 --> 00:14:25,114
Then take the leap
and promise me something

179
00:14:25,197 --> 00:14:27,616
now that you've made up your mind
to try this with me.

180
00:14:28,701 --> 00:14:29,869
What do you mean?

181
00:14:30,244 --> 00:14:32,538
Well, whether
we're actually dating or not...

182
00:14:34,081 --> 00:14:36,584
Right, we should do what needs to be done.

183
00:14:37,710 --> 00:14:39,420
Do what? My goodness.

184
00:14:39,503 --> 00:14:42,131
Gosh, do I look that easy to you?

185
00:14:43,215 --> 00:14:44,842
Are you a teenager or what?

186
00:14:45,009 --> 00:14:45,843
What?

187
00:14:45,926 --> 00:14:48,512
I guess you're very interested
in that field these days.

188
00:14:49,430 --> 00:14:52,182
Then what are you talking about?
What kind of promise?

189
00:14:56,312 --> 00:14:57,438
Just know

190
00:14:58,522 --> 00:15:03,360
that I'll always be within a 400-meter
radius from you from now on.

191
00:15:05,779 --> 00:15:08,616
On days that you feel down or upset,

192
00:15:08,699 --> 00:15:11,118
don't be sad all alone.

193
00:15:11,535 --> 00:15:15,247
All you need to do
is run to me right away.

194
00:15:17,791 --> 00:15:18,918
Just promise me

195
00:15:20,127 --> 00:15:21,211
that one thing.

196
00:15:24,673 --> 00:15:25,716
Let's make it official.

197
00:15:33,182 --> 00:15:34,308
Let's pinky swear.

198
00:15:48,614 --> 00:15:49,740
I promise.

199
00:15:57,039 --> 00:15:59,333
-And about Mr. No...
-Yes.

200
00:16:00,459 --> 00:16:01,961
THE ONGSAN FAIRY

201
00:16:02,044 --> 00:16:03,212
The thing is...

202
00:16:09,343 --> 00:16:12,262
Why don't you just pull out a tooth
with a cavity or something?

203
00:16:12,346 --> 00:16:15,015
I was born with super healthy teeth,
so it's fine.

204
00:16:15,099 --> 00:16:18,936
If you want to keep your job, you need
to make it look like it was mutual.

205
00:16:20,479 --> 00:16:23,774
Is it good? Are you enjoying your noodles?

206
00:16:24,149 --> 00:16:25,818
You're here to eat this, aren't you?

207
00:16:27,236 --> 00:16:28,570
I've been told to do nothing.

208
00:16:30,114 --> 00:16:30,948
By whom?

209
00:16:32,241 --> 00:16:34,743
Dongbaek. She said she'll take care of it.

210
00:16:34,827 --> 00:16:36,704
Dongbaek? What's she going to do?

211
00:16:37,705 --> 00:16:39,790
She'll press charges too
and call it even?

212
00:16:40,791 --> 00:16:43,085
I don't know.
She just said she'll take care of it.

213
00:16:47,464 --> 00:16:49,550
I believe her for some odd reason.

214
00:16:50,676 --> 00:16:52,428
Yesterday, I noticed

215
00:16:53,762 --> 00:16:55,472
that she's changed a little.

216
00:16:58,726 --> 00:17:00,811
Does Ongsan have that effect on people?

217
00:17:04,064 --> 00:17:06,191
I feel like all the women here

218
00:17:07,317 --> 00:17:09,445
are learning something on their own.

219
00:17:09,528 --> 00:17:12,823
CAMELLIA
FOR LEASE, AVAILABLE IMMEDIATELY

220
00:17:14,324 --> 00:17:16,076
One, two, three, four.

221
00:17:16,410 --> 00:17:18,078
Four exclamation marks.

222
00:17:22,124 --> 00:17:23,751
Hello, this is Camellia.

223
00:17:25,586 --> 00:17:26,462
Pardon me?

224
00:17:27,337 --> 00:17:28,338
Oh, hello.

225
00:17:29,381 --> 00:17:31,341
I scanned and saved everything in it.

226
00:17:31,425 --> 00:17:33,177
I e-mailed you the file.

227
00:17:33,802 --> 00:17:35,220
But why are you doing this?

228
00:17:35,304 --> 00:17:36,930
LAWYER HONG JA-YEONG

229
00:17:37,014 --> 00:17:39,016
You can't rely on these pieces of paper.

230
00:17:39,224 --> 00:17:41,560
If someone runs away with it,
you'll have nothing.

231
00:17:44,605 --> 00:17:47,900
So you're really helping me
press charges against your husband?

232
00:17:49,568 --> 00:17:52,154
To be honest, I just wrote stuff
like writing a diary.

233
00:17:52,279 --> 00:17:53,697
I just needed to vent.

234
00:17:54,490 --> 00:17:56,867
Record things properly
whatever that is for.

235
00:17:57,409 --> 00:18:00,329
Make sure everyone knows
that you have that thing.

236
00:18:00,788 --> 00:18:01,789
Sorry?

237
00:18:02,414 --> 00:18:04,416
Don't rumors follow everywhere you go?

238
00:18:04,583 --> 00:18:06,960
I'm sure they've always worked
to your disadvantage.

239
00:18:07,211 --> 00:18:08,754
It's time you benefited from them.

240
00:18:10,506 --> 00:18:12,216
I'm not really following.

241
00:18:12,299 --> 00:18:16,929
Just think that you're carrying a sword.

242
00:18:17,638 --> 00:18:22,518
If anyone provokes you, just bite
that person instead of squirming.

243
00:18:24,520 --> 00:18:26,772
I heard she has a ledger
about people's faults.

244
00:18:26,855 --> 00:18:29,441
I heard that power is shifting now.

245
00:18:29,525 --> 00:18:31,235
"Restaurant C's guest log.

246
00:18:31,318 --> 00:18:34,696
August 14, 2019. Farewell party
for Mr. Park in the secretary's office.

247
00:18:34,780 --> 00:18:36,824
Mixed shots of hard liquor and beer--"

248
00:18:36,907 --> 00:18:39,660
Wait. Anything about
the state I was in that day?

249
00:18:39,743 --> 00:18:40,828
You were dead drunk.

250
00:18:41,787 --> 00:18:44,039
"Dead drunk"? Damn it.

251
00:18:44,832 --> 00:18:46,375
What were you guys doing?

252
00:18:46,458 --> 00:18:47,960
-We were mixing the drinks.
-What?

253
00:18:48,460 --> 00:18:51,338
Did I hire you guys to mix drinks for me?

254
00:18:51,421 --> 00:18:53,340
We only did it
because you told us to, sir.

255
00:18:53,924 --> 00:18:57,678
What else? Did I talk nonsense

256
00:18:58,762 --> 00:18:59,763
or do anything stupid?

257
00:19:00,430 --> 00:19:02,182
No, sir.

