00:19:02,641 --> 00:19:04,893
But you left your autograph
on the wall there.

259
00:19:04,977 --> 00:19:08,355
I've signed my autograph
hundreds of times,

260
00:19:08,438 --> 00:19:10,232
so I couldn't have made any mistakes.

261
00:19:10,899 --> 00:19:12,901
The thing is, you wrote
something else.

262
00:19:12,985 --> 00:19:14,069
What did I write?

263
00:19:14,153 --> 00:19:17,156
Depending on how it's interpreted,
it could be seen as a little...

264
00:19:17,823 --> 00:19:19,741
-What?
-A little...

265
00:19:21,660 --> 00:19:23,871
It could be seen as dirty talk
in my opinion.

266
00:19:25,289 --> 00:19:26,456
What exactly did I write?

267
00:19:27,332 --> 00:19:29,835
Million-dollar legs!

268
00:19:29,918 --> 00:19:31,211
DONGBAEK
MILLION-DOLLAR LEGS

269
00:19:31,295 --> 00:19:34,089
With your signature underneath.

270
00:19:34,173 --> 00:19:35,257
What do you think?

271
00:19:36,091 --> 00:19:39,094
Should I report this to the party first?

272
00:19:47,060 --> 00:19:48,478
Is he going to settle with her?

273
00:19:48,645 --> 00:19:50,355
Gyu-tae, go and beg her.

274
00:19:50,439 --> 00:19:53,442
It's not like you went to jail
while fighting for democracy.

275
00:19:53,525 --> 00:19:57,362
Who'd want to vote for you
if you went to jail

276
00:19:57,446 --> 00:19:59,072
for touching a bar lady's hands?

277
00:20:00,407 --> 00:20:02,826
His political career will be over.

278
00:20:02,910 --> 00:20:03,952
This is all...

279
00:20:06,413 --> 00:20:07,873
political maneuvering.

280
00:20:09,416 --> 00:20:13,962
This is considered defamation of
a public figure and political maneuver.

281
00:20:14,046 --> 00:20:16,298
Even Clinton won the reelection.

282
00:20:16,465 --> 00:20:18,967
This won't be able to harm my future.

283
00:20:19,051 --> 00:20:20,469
Are you Bill Clinton?

284
00:20:20,552 --> 00:20:23,096
Ongsan people are not
as forgiving as those in the US.

285
00:20:23,180 --> 00:20:24,514
I will go my way.

286
00:20:24,598 --> 00:20:27,768
The horse can't go forward
if you turn around every time a dog barks.

287
00:20:29,269 --> 00:20:31,146
What? What are you saying?

288
00:20:31,521 --> 00:20:32,773
He can't even talk now.

289
00:20:33,815 --> 00:20:35,734
I'm totally fine.

290
00:20:36,276 --> 00:20:38,904
I'll stay composed
and keep my horse moving forward--

291
00:20:38,987 --> 00:20:40,197
-Okay, go!
-What?

292
00:20:40,489 --> 00:20:42,199
Carry on. We have to work.

293
00:20:42,282 --> 00:20:45,285
Stop wasting your time here
and go ride your horse, you fool.

294
00:20:45,369 --> 00:20:46,370
I should--

295
00:20:46,453 --> 00:20:49,248
Why are you standing
on my dried radish greens?

296
00:20:51,166 --> 00:20:52,626
You started talking to me first.

297
00:20:52,709 --> 00:20:56,129
We were chatting among ourselves.
You're going the wrong way. It's this way.

298
00:20:56,296 --> 00:20:58,799
-Giddy up!
-Hey, your zipper is down.

299
00:21:07,015 --> 00:21:08,600
Shit.

300
00:21:12,938 --> 00:21:15,565
Are you looking for the ledger?
She took it with her.

301
00:21:16,942 --> 00:21:18,777
Gosh.

302
00:21:18,860 --> 00:21:22,030
Is that a handbag or something?
Why does she have to carry it around?

303
00:21:22,239 --> 00:21:24,449
Were you going to steal it?

304
00:21:24,992 --> 00:21:27,244
You know that's stealing, right?

305
00:21:27,953 --> 00:21:29,955
At least you can't say such things to me.

306
00:21:30,998 --> 00:21:33,417
Give me the money for my plane ticket
by this Friday.

307
00:21:35,127 --> 00:21:38,463
Gosh. Do I need to do an exorcism
or something?

308
00:21:38,880 --> 00:21:41,258
I get it that you're going through
a hard time,

309
00:21:41,341 --> 00:21:44,553
-but you aren't the only one, you know.
-Hey, you.

310
00:21:45,470 --> 00:21:49,099
Are you picking a fight with me?
Is that it?

311
00:21:51,810 --> 00:21:54,021
Hey, why did you have to hit my head?

312
00:21:54,438 --> 00:21:56,565
Get out of the way. I have dementia.

313
00:21:56,648 --> 00:21:59,693
By the way,
why are you doing all this for me?

314
00:22:05,532 --> 00:22:06,366
No special reason.

315
00:22:07,326 --> 00:22:09,494
I can't help but observe you.

316
00:22:12,289 --> 00:22:14,541
You pique people's interest, you know.

317
00:22:16,501 --> 00:22:17,711
But why would you help me?

318
00:22:21,214 --> 00:22:22,382
By the way,

319
00:22:24,384 --> 00:22:25,427
what eye cream...

320
00:22:27,637 --> 00:22:29,681
No, never mind.

321
00:22:30,682 --> 00:22:32,976
HONG JA-YEONG LAW OFFICE

322
00:22:35,312 --> 00:22:38,774
Is she really going to side with Dongbaek
or what?

323
00:22:39,483 --> 00:22:40,525
Hang on.

324
00:22:42,235 --> 00:22:45,072
Shall I just blame everything
on this medication?

325
00:22:54,873 --> 00:22:57,167
Hey! Wait.

326
00:22:57,751 --> 00:22:59,503
Why are you coming out of there?

327
00:23:00,879 --> 00:23:05,300
Why did you meet with my wife?
Are you two ganging up on me or what?

328
00:23:06,051 --> 00:23:07,386
I saw her for a consultation.

329
00:23:09,554 --> 00:23:11,723
Is that your treasure? Let me see.

330
00:23:11,807 --> 00:23:13,892
-My gosh.
-Why are you holding it in your arms?

331
00:23:15,394 --> 00:23:17,104
It's mine, so mind your own business.

332
00:23:20,565 --> 00:23:21,566
Hey!

333
00:23:26,530 --> 00:23:27,656
Have some shaved ice.

334
00:23:34,538 --> 00:23:36,873
You don't quite understand
the situation right now.

335
00:23:36,957 --> 00:23:39,584
I'm going to press charges
against Yong-sik as well.

336
00:23:39,668 --> 00:23:42,546
I can prove what he did
because my dental implant fell out.

337
00:23:44,381 --> 00:23:45,966
I have proof, too.

338
00:23:47,259 --> 00:23:48,427
You're one gutsy woman.

339
00:23:49,636 --> 00:23:50,637
How...

340
00:23:51,388 --> 00:23:53,181
You can't do this
to your landlord.

341
00:23:55,058 --> 00:23:55,892
I can.

342
00:23:57,519 --> 00:23:58,395
What?

343
00:23:59,938 --> 00:24:01,523
"If you're rude, I'll be rude."

344
00:24:02,899 --> 00:24:04,484
That's my life's motto from now on.

345
00:24:10,031 --> 00:24:12,868
As they say, "You avoid poop because
it's scary, not dirty."

346
00:24:13,285 --> 00:24:16,413
Shit. I said it the other way around.

347
00:24:20,500 --> 00:24:22,169
If you're scared, just apologize.

348
00:24:22,252 --> 00:24:25,672
Forget it. I'll let this one slide
as I am a public figure,

349
00:24:25,797 --> 00:24:28,091
so let's both drop the charges.

350
00:24:28,550 --> 00:24:29,384
Apologize.

351
00:24:30,051 --> 00:24:31,553
Can't you grasp the situation?

352
00:24:31,928 --> 00:24:33,889
The fact is that
Yong-sik punched me first.

353
00:24:35,182 --> 00:24:38,226
And my molar has fallen out
because of that.

354
00:24:38,935 --> 00:24:41,563
-Just apologize.
-No, I won't. I refuse.

355
00:24:55,368 --> 00:24:56,828
I have a scanned copy of this

356
00:24:57,621 --> 00:25:00,332
in a flash drive, and another copy of it
in my email.

357
00:25:01,708 --> 00:25:04,211
Are you all going to college or something?

358
00:25:04,503 --> 00:25:06,296
How come everyone is so smart?

359
00:25:06,796 --> 00:25:08,089
See you in court.

360
00:25:33,114 --> 00:25:35,700
-Stop talking down to me.
-I'm just speaking English.

361
00:25:41,998 --> 00:25:43,166
I'm truly sorry.

362
00:25:43,500 --> 00:25:44,793
I'm very sorry.

363
00:25:45,752 --> 00:25:46,586
Happy now?

364
00:25:49,422 --> 00:25:51,258
Don't ever mess with me again.

365
00:25:52,842 --> 00:25:55,554
What's with you? Are you high?

366
00:25:56,429 --> 00:25:59,057
The trigger has been pulled,
and the old Dongbaek is dead.

367
00:25:59,140 --> 00:26:01,810
So from now on,
if you even mention peanuts, I will

368
00:26:03,061 --> 00:26:04,062
shoot.

369
00:26:08,567 --> 00:26:12,070
Did you get a prescription
from the neurosurgeon at the intersection?

370
00:26:14,698 --> 00:26:17,200
I'm going to shoot you without hesitating.

371
00:26:20,453 --> 00:26:22,372
I'm so not used to this.

372
00:26:23,206 --> 00:26:25,542
It's not easy for me
to become so tough overnight.

373
00:26:29,254 --> 00:26:30,213
Hello.

374
00:26:32,299 --> 00:26:34,759
That must be the ledger.

375
00:26:35,552 --> 00:26:37,679
I can't believe that girl.

376
00:26:37,762 --> 00:26:39,180
I can't believe her.

377
00:26:45,770 --> 00:26:49,190
I can't believe she wrote that
behind everyone's back.

378
00:26:49,399 --> 00:26:51,651
-That absolutely...
-Serves them right.

379
00:26:53,737 --> 00:26:57,574
It serves those ungrateful men right
to be afraid of her ledger.

380
00:26:57,866 --> 00:27:00,827
Dongbaek can be pretty sly.

381
00:27:01,953 --> 00:27:03,038
It's a compliment.

382
00:27:04,247 --> 00:27:05,457
It's great.

383
00:27:07,792 --> 00:27:09,336
RESIDENTS WITHIN THE JURISDICTION

384
00:27:10,670 --> 00:27:12,964
You call this cooperation?

385
00:27:14,674 --> 00:27:17,844
So are you telling us

386
00:27:18,386 --> 00:27:20,972
to investigate every single person

387
00:27:21,056 --> 00:27:23,558
within the jurisdiction
who wears 260mm size shoes?

388
00:27:23,642 --> 00:27:25,560
Didn't you see Unanswered Questions?

389
00:27:25,644 --> 00:27:27,812
The footprint
found on the scene was 260mm.

390
00:27:28,229 --> 00:27:31,858
In that case, we'll have to start
with kids who are around 15,

391
00:27:31,983 --> 00:27:35,070
and we'll have to check everyone
who's alive above that age.

392
00:27:36,529 --> 00:27:39,491
And we don't have enough manpower to...

393
00:27:40,367 --> 00:27:41,368
Good luck.

394
00:27:42,494 --> 00:27:44,663
-What?
-I'm bidding you good luck.

395
00:27:57,842 --> 00:28:00,345
Goodness, your shoes are size 260mm, too.

396
00:28:01,054 --> 00:28:02,430
Suspect number one.

397
00:28:04,182 --> 00:28:06,810
I mean, does he think this is the 80s?

398
00:28:06,893 --> 00:28:08,770
We need a scientific investigation.

399
00:28:08,853 --> 00:28:12,440
Even if we do that, you won't be
a part of it. Scientific guys will do it.

400
00:28:12,524 --> 00:28:14,567
I can't approve
of an investigation like this.

401
00:28:14,734 --> 00:28:16,695
Did anyone ask for your approval?

402
00:28:16,986 --> 00:28:20,657
This kind of sloppy investigation is
unthinkable in Miami.

403
00:28:20,740 --> 00:28:22,033
Then go there.

404
00:28:22,701 --> 00:28:25,453
Stop giving us headaches
and transfer to the Miami office.

405
00:28:25,995 --> 00:28:27,080
What? What now?

406
00:28:27,163 --> 00:28:29,874
Do I have to go door-to-door
measuring people's feet?

407
00:28:30,250 --> 00:28:31,626
You should

408
00:28:32,210 --> 00:28:34,838
turn in an application
to the Miami precinct.

409
00:28:35,046 --> 00:28:37,882
If you want to do that,
I'll write you a recommendation letter.

410
00:28:40,802 --> 00:28:42,595
You can measure people's feet.

411
00:28:43,179 --> 00:28:44,556
I'll do my own investigation.

412
00:28:44,639 --> 00:28:46,683
Smart people
couldn't catch him for six years.

413
00:28:46,766 --> 00:28:47,851
What can you do?

414
00:28:47,934 --> 00:28:50,937
I have a quality they don't have.

415
00:28:51,020 --> 00:28:52,397
What do you have?

416
00:28:53,356 --> 00:28:55,358
Who in the world do you think you are?

417
00:28:56,860 --> 00:28:59,487
Me? I'm a native.

418
00:29:01,614 --> 00:29:02,615
What?

419
00:29:04,242 --> 00:29:05,785
I'm a native of Ongsan.

420
00:29:10,206 --> 00:29:12,292
If you've attended middle
and high school here,

421
00:29:12,417 --> 00:29:14,502
you're pretty much
a family member here.

422
00:29:14,794 --> 00:29:18,256
Everyone is a brother, a sister,
an aunt, or an uncle of someone you know.

423
00:29:18,339 --> 00:29:20,717
The system is kind of like
a group of mafia bosses.

424
00:29:22,051 --> 00:29:25,555
Hey, do you think my eyebrows look uneven?

425
00:29:25,638 --> 00:29:26,806
-Yes.
-Hey.

426
00:29:26,890 --> 00:29:28,850
My husband is definitely cheating on me.

427
00:29:29,058 --> 00:29:31,394
-You really can't arrest him for that?
-Ladies here

428
00:29:31,478 --> 00:29:34,314
-tell me just about anything.
-Forget it!

429
00:29:35,190 --> 00:29:37,150
What you're doing could be seen as...

430
00:29:37,233 --> 00:29:38,818
And in this town...

431
00:29:38,902 --> 00:29:41,529
Even if you put me behind bars,
I won't say a word.

432
00:29:41,613 --> 00:29:43,656
People are aggressively mean to outsiders.

433
00:29:46,534 --> 00:29:49,496
Why are they asking us about Joker
when they failed to catch him?

434
00:29:49,579 --> 00:29:51,706
-Goodness.
-What do you think they're doing?

435
00:29:52,290 --> 00:29:55,752
They're just causing mayhem in the
neighborhood and dropping our land value.

436
00:29:55,835 --> 00:29:57,337
-Say that again.
-That's it.

437
00:29:57,420 --> 00:29:58,546
Don't say anything.

438
00:29:59,589 --> 00:30:02,258
We'll all say that we don't know a thing.

439
00:30:02,342 --> 00:30:04,844
-Let's all do that.
-We'll all do that.

440
00:30:04,928 --> 00:30:06,638
What do you mean, you'll all do that?

441
00:30:06,763 --> 00:30:08,681
It's not like you know something.

442
00:30:09,140 --> 00:30:10,016
-What?
-What?

443
00:30:10,600 --> 00:30:13,645
Of course, we do. We know everything.

444
00:30:14,062 --> 00:30:15,396
-We do.
-We know everything.

445
00:30:16,064 --> 00:30:18,483
What do you know? You always say that.

446
00:30:19,108 --> 00:30:19,943
Hey.

447
00:30:20,985 --> 00:30:23,947
You haven't sat around here
365 days a year.

448
00:30:24,656 --> 00:30:27,617
We even know stuff like
whose earthen pot got chipped.

449
00:30:28,243 --> 00:30:30,870
-We know everything.
-We know everything.

450
00:30:33,832 --> 00:30:35,250
Then who's Joker?

451
00:30:36,042 --> 00:30:38,253
-Joker?
-Joker?

452
00:30:39,546 --> 00:30:40,630
Joker is...

453
00:30:52,600 --> 00:30:53,935
INTESTINE MEDICINE

454
00:31:02,026 --> 00:31:02,902
What's in Ongsan?

455
00:31:04,487 --> 00:31:05,905
SPEEDING TICKET

456
00:31:08,449 --> 00:31:10,034
Get your act together.

457
00:31:10,118 --> 00:31:13,621
I'm joining you this time
for your water purifier ad,

458
00:31:13,705 --> 00:31:17,250
so if you get in trouble for DUI
or speeding, you'll be a nuisance to me.

459
00:31:18,167 --> 00:31:19,502
You're doing it with me?

460
00:31:20,003 --> 00:31:21,379
Hey, why would do that?

461
00:31:22,797 --> 00:31:24,799
Do you know
how scary the public is nowadays?

462
00:31:25,091 --> 00:31:25,925
Whatever.

463
00:31:26,259 --> 00:31:28,595
Why do you try so hard to get disliked?

464
00:31:29,512 --> 00:31:30,972
People like me.

465
00:31:31,264 --> 00:31:33,975
I get over 600 likes
whenever I post a picture.

466
00:31:34,100 --> 00:31:35,894
Are you a celebrity or an athlete?

467
00:31:35,977 --> 00:31:39,439
What in the world are you?
How can an unemployed person film an ad?

468
00:31:39,522 --> 00:31:42,233
Well, I was annoyed
about you calling me unemployed.

469
00:31:43,234 --> 00:31:44,819
I told you to be more respectful.

470
00:31:47,405 --> 00:31:48,406
I'm going to Milan.

471
00:31:49,282 --> 00:31:51,117
-What?
-I'm going there in November.

472
00:31:52,660 --> 00:31:54,454
Gosh, you're so laid-back.

473
00:31:54,537 --> 00:31:56,789
What about our kid? Why you travel--

474
00:31:56,873 --> 00:31:59,334
No, it's not a trip. I'm studying abroad.

475
00:32:00,293 --> 00:32:02,003
A modeling school for two years.

476
00:32:02,629 --> 00:32:03,630
Two years?

477
00:32:04,005 --> 00:32:06,716
Wait, you're going to abandon your kid
and leave for two--

478
00:32:06,799 --> 00:32:08,259
I'm not abandoning her.

479
00:32:08,343 --> 00:32:09,385
She has her loving dad,

480
00:32:09,469 --> 00:32:12,722
her grandmother, and her nanny,
so I can be away for two years.

481
00:32:13,306 --> 00:32:16,476
Wait. Do you know
how much she needs you right now?

482
00:32:16,559 --> 00:32:17,977
She can't remember anyway.

483
00:32:18,561 --> 00:32:19,979
You remember when you were one?

484
00:32:23,024 --> 00:32:25,234
Don't you have any maternal instinct?

485
00:32:25,318 --> 00:32:27,820
A mom needs to be successful
for her child to be happy.

486
00:32:31,908 --> 00:32:33,034
That delivery guy.

487
00:32:33,826 --> 00:32:36,746
That rude delivery guy
of Dongwon Chinese Food.

488
00:32:37,497 --> 00:32:39,290
He was one unusual guy.

489
00:32:39,374 --> 00:32:40,833
Definitely, yes.

490
00:32:41,084 --> 00:32:45,463
I believe he stole
my husband's motorbike, too.

491
00:32:45,546 --> 00:32:48,216
-Right.
-You're right.

492
00:32:48,883 --> 00:32:53,429
Then he would've been
one of the key suspects, right?

493
00:32:53,513 --> 00:32:54,639
-Yes.
-Right.

494
00:32:54,722 --> 00:32:57,058
-But he died.
-What?

495
00:32:57,141 --> 00:32:59,894
He was the second person
that Joker killed.

496
00:33:01,938 --> 00:33:03,356
So it was a misunderstanding.

497
00:33:03,898 --> 00:33:05,817
-We feel kind of bad.
-Right.

498
00:33:05,900 --> 00:33:07,819
-You're right.
-We're sorry.

499
00:33:09,028 --> 00:33:10,029
A misunderstanding.

500
00:33:11,823 --> 00:33:13,866
Then who's Joker?

501
00:33:15,368 --> 00:33:16,452
I think

502
00:33:17,328 --> 00:33:19,038
it's the guy at the fortune-teller's.

503
00:33:21,541 --> 00:33:23,626
That vicious-looking guy
who visited her often?

504
00:33:23,710 --> 00:33:25,211
-Yes.
-That evil-looking guy?

505
00:33:25,294 --> 00:33:26,796
-Yes.
-That guy.

506
00:33:26,879 --> 00:33:31,217
The case broke out
whenever he came into town.

507
00:33:31,300 --> 00:33:33,720
-You're right.
-Yes, you're right.

508
00:33:33,803 --> 00:33:35,054
This is a good point.

509
00:33:35,138 --> 00:33:37,598
Then is that vicious-looking guy--

510
00:33:37,682 --> 00:33:40,560
