00:33:41,936 --> 00:33:43,980
When people were dying in Ongsan,

513
00:33:44,063 --> 00:33:47,358
he was catching mackerels in Norway.

514
00:33:47,442 --> 00:33:49,444
-Norway?
-I mean, he was in Norway.

515
00:33:49,527 --> 00:33:51,738
-In Norway.
-We can't help it if he was there.

516
00:33:51,821 --> 00:33:53,740
-He was in Norway.
-In Norway.

517
00:33:54,115 --> 00:33:56,325
He was diligent, after all.

518
00:34:00,371 --> 00:34:02,915
Why do you keep saying nonsense?

519
00:34:03,541 --> 00:34:05,877
You say someone stole a motorbike
and looks vicious,

520
00:34:05,960 --> 00:34:08,504
but that's all subjective.
It's not clear evidence.

521
00:34:08,588 --> 00:34:10,923
Tell me objective circumstantial evidence.

522
00:34:11,007 --> 00:34:13,551
-The Norway guy--
-Forget the Norway guy.

523
00:34:13,676 --> 00:34:16,304
Norway, that darned Norway.

524
00:34:16,387 --> 00:34:18,681
If I know that,
why would I be selling rice cake?

525
00:34:18,765 --> 00:34:22,185
You would sell rice cake
while she's the head of the investigation.

526
00:34:22,268 --> 00:34:23,186
She's right.

527
00:34:25,646 --> 00:34:28,441
Forget it. What was I expecting?

528
00:34:29,484 --> 00:34:32,028
Hey, forget it. This is over. Go.

529
00:34:32,111 --> 00:34:34,697
You should get back to your businesses.

530
00:34:34,781 --> 00:34:38,034
There is one guy who made money
after the murder case.

531
00:34:38,534 --> 00:34:40,536
-There is.
-Yes, there is.

532
00:34:42,371 --> 00:34:43,206
Gyu-tae.

533
00:34:44,499 --> 00:34:45,541
No Gyu-tae?

534
00:34:45,666 --> 00:34:46,876
OK AESTHETIC

535
00:34:46,959 --> 00:34:50,588
Gyu-tae pretty much bought the
Ok Aesthetic building for free.

536
00:34:51,255 --> 00:34:53,841
I didn't know why he bought a building
where someone died,

537
00:34:54,092 --> 00:34:56,844
but after a year, the terminal
moved to behind that building.

538
00:34:57,553 --> 00:34:59,597
Who knows if he knew something

539
00:34:59,680 --> 00:35:01,849
or if he just got lucky with money?

540
00:35:04,936 --> 00:35:07,313
Why would you go to Milan? Why?

541
00:35:08,773 --> 00:35:09,690
Quiet.

542
00:35:10,358 --> 00:35:12,318
You aren't a real model
or a fashion major.

543
00:35:12,401 --> 00:35:14,070
Why would you suddenly go to Milan?

544
00:35:14,153 --> 00:35:16,364
That camera can record sounds, too.

545
00:35:16,656 --> 00:35:19,325
You know that this is
kind of like your name, don't you?

546
00:35:19,408 --> 00:35:21,452
You lived your whole life
in Jeolla Province,

547
00:35:21,536 --> 00:35:24,163
but your name is Jessica,
so it's kind of like that.

548
00:35:26,290 --> 00:35:27,917
I'm a New Yorker.

549
00:35:28,042 --> 00:35:29,919
I've been Jessica ever since I was there.

550
00:35:30,503 --> 00:35:32,255
You were there for only three months.

551
00:35:32,338 --> 00:35:34,382
Then am I Japanese
since I played for Yomiuri?

552
00:35:34,465 --> 00:35:36,008
-Shut up.
-You can't go.

553
00:35:36,092 --> 00:35:37,844
I have no money for you to study.

554
00:35:37,927 --> 00:35:40,221
Then we can get divorced,
and I'll get alimony.

555
00:35:40,304 --> 00:35:42,515
-Park Sang-mi!
-What, Kang Jong-ryeol?

556
00:35:50,481 --> 00:35:53,025
Fine, go study abroad or whatever.

557
00:35:53,442 --> 00:35:56,863
I'll let you do it.
But leave after Ji-seon is a bit older.

558
00:35:56,946 --> 00:35:59,782
Stop trying to clip my wings
by using Rebecca as an excuse!

559
00:35:59,866 --> 00:36:03,161
She's not Rebecca! She's Kang Ji-seon,
Kang Jong-ryeol's daughter!

560
00:36:03,244 --> 00:36:05,788
And you're Park Sang-mi!
Park Sang-mi!

561
00:36:07,832 --> 00:36:08,666
Stop the car.

562
00:36:10,626 --> 00:36:12,962
You'll die of embarrassment
in just ten years.

563
00:36:13,546 --> 00:36:16,424
People make fun of stars for life
for something stupid they did.

564
00:36:16,674 --> 00:36:18,342
You need to grow up!

565
00:36:18,426 --> 00:36:20,178
I said, stop the car!

566
00:36:35,610 --> 00:36:37,069
I shouldn't go there.

567
00:36:38,779 --> 00:36:40,031
I shouldn't.

568
00:36:42,867 --> 00:36:47,288
I found my crazy escape
in an absurd place.

569
00:36:51,250 --> 00:36:52,668
MATH QUIZ

570
00:36:52,752 --> 00:36:55,296
If he does this badly in math
during his first year,

571
00:36:55,379 --> 00:36:57,423
it'll only get worse as he grows.

572
00:37:00,718 --> 00:37:04,847
But Pil-gu is better at math than I was.

573
00:37:05,514 --> 00:37:06,349
Pardon?

574
00:37:07,475 --> 00:37:11,437
I think it's okay for him
to not try so hard

575
00:37:11,520 --> 00:37:15,191
to get good grades on math
if it's too hard for him.

576
00:37:16,817 --> 00:37:17,944
I see.

577
00:37:18,527 --> 00:37:19,904
What I want to know

578
00:37:20,613 --> 00:37:22,365
isn't his math grade.

579
00:37:23,824 --> 00:37:26,994
I want to know
how he gets along with others.

580
00:37:27,578 --> 00:37:29,747
Just because his mom runs a bar...

581
00:37:30,081 --> 00:37:33,709
Does he get made fun of? Or...

582
00:37:34,085 --> 00:37:35,544
Because he doesn't have a dad...

583
00:37:36,254 --> 00:37:38,089
Or if he gets intimidated and such.

584
00:37:39,340 --> 00:37:41,592
He sometimes comes home after a fight.

585
00:37:42,510 --> 00:37:45,846
Pil-gu isn't the side that gets beaten up.

586
00:37:56,607 --> 00:37:57,483
Mr. Kang.

587
00:37:57,984 --> 00:38:01,153
Hello. You come here pretty often.

588
00:38:01,320 --> 00:38:04,365
Are you conducting
some business over here?

589
00:38:04,949 --> 00:38:07,493
I can poop whenever I come to this school.

590
00:38:08,244 --> 00:38:09,120
What?

591
00:38:09,245 --> 00:38:11,956
My mind blanks out,
but my organs work well.

592
00:38:12,456 --> 00:38:14,333
My heart feels tense,

593
00:38:15,001 --> 00:38:17,670
but I only feel at peace
after seeing it with my eyes.

594
00:38:21,090 --> 00:38:24,010
So you come all the way to Ongsan to poop?

595
00:38:32,727 --> 00:38:33,769
Goodness.

596
00:38:35,730 --> 00:38:39,483
Pil-gu. Why are you kicking the wall for?

597
00:38:39,567 --> 00:38:40,693
Do you play soccer?

598
00:38:40,776 --> 00:38:43,154
Why do I have to write
my journals in English?

599
00:38:44,363 --> 00:38:45,990
I didn't because I'm a patriot.

600
00:38:47,199 --> 00:38:49,035
So what? Should I get your mom?

601
00:38:50,244 --> 00:38:52,079
I already told you hundreds of times.

602
00:38:52,621 --> 00:38:54,957
My mom is a working mom. A working mom!

603
00:38:58,794 --> 00:39:01,547
-Why does he have my temper, too?
-What is he saying?

604
00:39:01,630 --> 00:39:04,884
Man, that punk.
I wonder who he took after.

605
00:39:05,384 --> 00:39:06,969
Why do you care who he took after?

606
00:39:07,053 --> 00:39:10,556
A child is a human being, too.
Don't call him a punk.

607
00:39:13,392 --> 00:39:15,728
Is he a children's rights activist
or what?

608
00:39:25,821 --> 00:39:29,533
LET'S ALL MAKE
THE HAPPIEST SCHOOL IN THIS WORLD

609
00:39:31,994 --> 00:39:33,746
I'll become a major leaguer

610
00:39:33,829 --> 00:39:36,165
and make a huge bar for my mom.

611
00:39:36,665 --> 00:39:37,708
Kang Pil-gu.

612
00:39:38,626 --> 00:39:40,795
CAMELLIA

613
00:39:40,920 --> 00:39:42,296
Why is that tiny little kid

614
00:39:43,339 --> 00:39:45,132
so manly?

615
00:39:45,716 --> 00:39:47,259
That makes me want him even more.

616
00:39:50,262 --> 00:39:52,890
Is that why you've been
investigating Mr. No?

617
00:39:53,015 --> 00:39:54,100
You think he's Joker?

618
00:39:55,101 --> 00:39:58,521
Hey, do you think No Gyu-tae is
a guy who can kill a man?

619
00:39:59,897 --> 00:40:02,400
It's always like that. Always.

620
00:40:02,691 --> 00:40:04,026
On CSI,

621
00:40:04,110 --> 00:40:07,363
those who are the least likely
always end up getting arrested.

622
00:40:07,446 --> 00:40:10,908
Hey, No Gyu-tae suffered
from facial nerve palsy

623
00:40:10,991 --> 00:40:13,661
-after he hit an elk with his car.
-What?

624
00:40:13,744 --> 00:40:15,996
His mouth got droopy because of the shock.

625
00:40:16,414 --> 00:40:17,248
My gosh.

626
00:40:17,331 --> 00:40:19,583
Some even say that he got an exorcism

627
00:40:20,084 --> 00:40:22,169
because he had too many nightmares.

628
00:40:22,920 --> 00:40:25,089
That's how much of a coward he is.

629
00:40:25,172 --> 00:40:28,551
Did the elk trample him
in his nightmares or what?

630
00:40:28,843 --> 00:40:31,929
Man, that guy is really unbelievable.

631
00:40:32,805 --> 00:40:36,058
Anyway, he's really weird.

632
00:40:36,142 --> 00:40:38,519
He's right in the gray area

633
00:40:38,602 --> 00:40:43,190
between a bad guy and a fool.

634
00:40:43,315 --> 00:40:46,485
Hey, he isn't just a coward.
He's pretty stupid, too.

635
00:40:47,236 --> 00:40:49,447
And if Mr. No was Joker,

636
00:40:49,989 --> 00:40:52,616
he would have left
tons of evidence already.

637
00:40:52,700 --> 00:40:53,576
POLICE

638
00:40:53,742 --> 00:40:56,912
The building.
Why did he buy that building?

639
00:40:56,996 --> 00:40:59,915
It show he's the only one
who made money thanks to Joker.

640
00:40:59,999 --> 00:41:03,836
Hey. It was sold at half
its original price because of the murder.

641
00:41:04,295 --> 00:41:06,547
I would've bought it as well
if I had the money.

642
00:41:07,798 --> 00:41:09,842
My gosh, then who is it?

643
00:41:10,676 --> 00:41:11,719
Darn it.

644
00:41:12,219 --> 00:41:15,181
Chief, let me be honest.

645
00:41:15,848 --> 00:41:19,018
I have absolutely no idea
whom it could be.

646
00:41:19,852 --> 00:41:21,061
My goodness.

647
00:41:21,770 --> 00:41:23,355
It's normal for you to be lost.

648
00:41:24,231 --> 00:41:25,483
When you're lost like that,

649
00:41:26,150 --> 00:41:28,068
you should go and see Yeong-sim.

650
00:41:28,777 --> 00:41:31,238
My goodness, I've heard enough of her.

651
00:41:32,448 --> 00:41:35,701
EVEN ELEMENTARY SCHOOL KIDS KNOW THIS
DRIVE SLOWLY IN FRONT OF A SCHOOL

652
00:41:45,503 --> 00:41:47,254
Look far ahead of you.

653
00:41:47,338 --> 00:41:48,506
Okay, next.

654
00:41:48,589 --> 00:41:52,551
Don't forget to go home
and tell your mothers about this.

655
00:41:53,427 --> 00:41:55,221
Okay, good job. Next.

656
00:41:55,804 --> 00:41:58,974
Tell them that Kang Jong-ryeol
gave you baseball lessons today.

657
00:41:59,308 --> 00:42:01,685
Tell them I arranged it for you, okay?

658
00:42:01,769 --> 00:42:02,603
-Okay.
-Okay.

659
00:42:02,686 --> 00:42:04,230
But to be honest,

660
00:42:04,313 --> 00:42:06,649
-we can't call this a lesson--
-Focus on the ball!

661
00:42:06,732 --> 00:42:08,526
Try that again. Go on.

662
00:42:11,904 --> 00:42:16,325
You need to stay balanced. Keep your legs
firmly on the ground. Again!

663
00:42:19,870 --> 00:42:23,666
Pil-gu, why are your arms so loose?
What's wrong with you? Again!

664
00:42:27,127 --> 00:42:29,838
Stop. Why do you always sigh
before you hit the ball?

665
00:42:29,922 --> 00:42:32,049
Is that some kind of routine you do?

666
00:42:32,591 --> 00:42:35,469
You think that's cool?
Where did you learn that kind of stuff?

667
00:42:37,263 --> 00:42:40,724
What about you? Why do you always
smell your helmet before you hit the ball?

668
00:42:41,559 --> 00:42:43,644
Do you know how disgusting that is?

669
00:42:46,146 --> 00:42:48,649
They say even teachers
can't teach their own kids.

670
00:42:51,569 --> 00:42:53,153
-Well...
-Mom!

671
00:42:54,822 --> 00:42:56,407
Mom!

672
00:42:57,283 --> 00:42:59,535
-Mom!
-It must be his mom.

673
00:43:01,579 --> 00:43:03,706
I'm surprised to see Dongbaek here.

674
00:43:04,748 --> 00:43:06,458
Is she your friend?

675
00:43:07,084 --> 00:43:08,961
She's a student's parent,
not your friend.

676
00:43:09,587 --> 00:43:11,714
You should have some manners.

677
00:43:14,425 --> 00:43:15,968
Who does he think he is?

678
00:43:16,218 --> 00:43:18,929
Mom!

679
00:43:19,430 --> 00:43:20,598
Mom!

680
00:43:21,765 --> 00:43:23,183
-Mom!
-What?

681
00:43:25,269 --> 00:43:27,521
Mom, didn't you hear me?

682
00:43:28,272 --> 00:43:30,316
I called you from
all the way from over there.

683
00:43:31,025 --> 00:43:33,235
No, I didn't hear you. You called me?

684
00:43:33,652 --> 00:43:35,988
Why did you run over here
in the middle of training?

685
00:43:36,071 --> 00:43:37,281
-Hello.
-Hello.

686
00:43:37,364 --> 00:43:39,658
Oh. Hi, guys.

687
00:43:40,701 --> 00:43:43,162
Mom, what's with your hair?

688
00:43:44,830 --> 00:43:48,250
-Why? Does it look weird?
-Why did you come here like that?

689
00:43:50,085 --> 00:43:51,462
I was just about to go.

690
00:43:51,545 --> 00:43:53,672
You guys should
get back to training. Go on.

691
00:43:54,506 --> 00:43:57,509
What did I tell you guys?
I told you that my mom's really pretty.

692
00:43:58,385 --> 00:44:00,220
She looks even prettier with a bun.

693
00:44:01,347 --> 00:44:03,098
Pil-gu never lies.

694
00:44:04,433 --> 00:44:07,394
I told them you're as pretty as Tzuyu,

695
00:44:07,645 --> 00:44:08,979
but they thought I was lying.

696
00:44:09,605 --> 00:44:13,025
That's why I always told you
to come and see me at school.

697
00:44:13,108 --> 00:44:14,777
But why with a ponytail?

698
00:44:15,110 --> 00:44:16,528
I told you to make a bun

699
00:44:17,196 --> 00:44:19,281
just like Dahyun.

700
00:44:19,365 --> 00:44:23,118
I came in such a hurry
that I totally forgot.

701
00:44:23,202 --> 00:44:24,787
I'll do it next time.

702
00:44:25,579 --> 00:44:26,705
By the way, Dong-gyu.

703
00:44:27,247 --> 00:44:30,292
You told me your dad's a vice president,
right? My mom's a CEO.

704
00:44:34,046 --> 00:44:36,465
My goodness, yes. I am a CEO.

705
00:44:37,341 --> 00:44:40,469
Do you guys want to eat ice cream?

706
00:44:40,552 --> 00:44:42,179
-Here.
-My mom bought these for us.

707
00:44:42,262 --> 00:44:45,724
-Thank you, ma'am.
-Thank you, ma'am.

708
00:44:45,808 --> 00:44:47,309
Don't mention it. Enjoy.

709
00:44:47,935 --> 00:44:49,019
Thanks, Pil-gu.

710
00:44:50,187 --> 00:44:52,439
What's he doing here again?

711
00:44:53,190 --> 00:44:54,191
Would you like one?

712
00:44:55,776 --> 00:44:58,237
-No, it's okay.
-You should have one.

713
00:45:00,864 --> 00:45:01,699
By any chance,

714
00:45:03,909 --> 00:45:05,577
do you have a chestnut-flavored one?

715
00:45:40,863 --> 00:45:42,698
I understand you're curious about Pil-gu

716
00:45:42,781 --> 00:45:45,659
because he's your son,
even though we didn't end on good terms.

717
00:45:47,911 --> 00:45:50,539
But you're really disrespecting your wife.

718
00:45:54,001 --> 00:45:56,754
How could you do
something like this to me?

719
00:45:57,171 --> 00:45:58,672
This is driving me crazy.

720
00:46:04,762 --> 00:46:07,139
If you care about him,
don't come here anymore.

721
00:46:07,890 --> 00:46:08,891
Instead,

722
00:46:10,100 --> 00:46:11,393
let me ask you for a favor.

723
00:46:12,436 --> 00:46:13,854
There's no need to ask.

724
00:46:14,146 --> 00:46:17,149
You probably know since it's on the web,
but I earn a lot of money.

725
00:46:17,691 --> 00:46:21,403
I heard the landlord asked you
to move out of the building.

726
00:46:22,404 --> 00:46:26,241
You know The Return of Superman?
Can you just quit that show?

727
00:46:26,909 --> 00:46:27,743
What?

728
00:46:27,868 --> 00:46:31,872
You take your daughter to go see dinosaurs
and go camping with her.

729
00:46:32,456 --> 00:46:35,751
Can't you at least do that much
for Pil-gu's sake?

730
00:46:37,127 --> 00:46:39,922
Why do you want me to quit the show?

731
00:46:42,341 --> 00:46:44,802
If he finds out
that the really kind dad on TV

732
00:46:44,885 --> 00:46:46,094
is actually his dad,

733
00:46:47,888 --> 00:46:49,348
it'll scar him.

734
00:46:56,563 --> 00:46:59,066
You already earn a lot of money
regardless of that show.

735
00:46:59,775 --> 00:47:02,319
You can do whatever you want,
but please quit that show.

736
00:47:02,402 --> 00:47:03,570
Please.

737
00:47:07,074 --> 00:47:07,991
What about you?

738
00:47:11,954 --> 00:47:13,372
Did it scar you as well?

739
00:47:22,297 --> 00:47:25,259
Why did you have to show up now
instead of when I looked for you?

740
00:47:27,135 --> 00:47:28,303
I know...

741
00:47:31,473 --> 00:47:33,433
I know I'm a real jerk for saying this.

742
00:47:35,769 --> 00:47:37,354
But now that I see you again...

743
00:47:39,273 --> 00:47:40,440
You and Pil-gu.

744
00:47:43,485 --> 00:47:44,862
How am I supposed to bear it?

745
00:47:47,906 --> 00:47:49,116
You haven't changed.

746
00:47:51,159 --> 00:47:52,244
You're still a jerk.

747
00:48:12,389 --> 00:48:15,767
Why did you have to like a jerk like me?

748
00:48:18,896 --> 00:48:21,732
Pil-gu will be here soon.
You should go now.

749
00:48:22,316 --> 00:48:24,568
Your bad taste in men
is what ruined your life.

750
00:48:26,987 --> 00:48:28,280
What's wrong with my life?

751
00:48:29,197 --> 00:48:30,741
My life isn't yours, you know.

752
00:48:32,284 --> 00:48:34,161
-What?
-I dated you because I liked you

753
00:48:34,244 --> 00:48:37,331
and had Pil-gu because I wanted to.
I'm the one who controls my life.

754
00:48:37,414 --> 00:48:39,499
I'm responsible
for everything that happened.

755
00:48:40,083 --> 00:48:42,127
Who do you think you are?

756
00:48:42,336 --> 00:48:45,756
Why do you think
you have control over my life?

757
00:48:50,677 --> 00:48:51,553
You

758
00:48:53,180 --> 00:48:54,890
kind of look really cool now.

759
00:48:55,349 --> 00:48:59,186
That's because I am cool.
I'm 173cm tall with a great body ratio.

760
00:48:59,937 --> 00:49:02,356
I have an amazing son,
and I'm the CEO of this bar.

761
00:49:03,065 --> 00:49:05,525
I was never a supporting role
of someone's life.

762
00:49:05,609 --> 00:49:07,402
I was always the lead actress.

763
00:49:09,071 --> 00:49:10,322
You must be dating him.

764
00:49:13,659 --> 00:49:16,536
Does that hillbilly make you cool?

765
00:49:20,499 --> 00:49:21,750
-Heung-sik, this way.
-Okay.

766
00:49:23,168 --> 00:49:24,336
Hi, Dongbaek.

767
00:49:37,057 --> 00:49:38,266
Hello.

768
00:49:39,101 --> 00:49:41,103
I'll install it over there.

769
00:49:49,569 --> 00:49:51,530
This shot is amazing.

770
00:49:52,906 --> 00:49:54,908
I'm glad I chose to work here.

771
00:49:54,992 --> 00:49:56,827
Don't step out of line.

772
00:49:59,746 --> 00:50:02,124
Pay 5,000 won. I added some honey too.

773
00:50:03,542 --> 00:50:04,668
He doesn't need to pay.

774
00:50:04,835 --> 00:50:07,212
Heung-sik, you should eat before you go.

775
00:50:07,295 --> 00:50:08,714
-Yes, you should.
-Okay.

776
00:50:08,797 --> 00:50:10,924
You're giving him free food?

777
00:50:11,008 --> 00:50:12,259
Why give him free food?

778
00:50:12,592 --> 00:50:14,469
She really does have mood swings.

779
00:50:15,929 --> 00:50:20,642
I always felt worried
leaving Pil-gu here all by himself.

780
00:50:21,435 --> 00:50:23,562
Thank you for being so considerate.

781
00:50:25,605 --> 00:50:26,857
I'd also like to thank you.

782
00:50:28,442 --> 00:50:29,568
Thank you.

783
00:50:30,986 --> 00:50:32,738
You don't need to thank me.

784
00:50:33,530 --> 00:50:36,658
No, I do want to thank you. Thanks a lot.

785
00:50:40,620 --> 00:50:44,041
Yong-sik, you just
got out of trouble yesterday.

786
00:50:45,375 --> 00:50:46,209
Dongbaek.

787
00:50:53,759 --> 00:50:54,593
Mr. Kang.

788
00:50:57,095 --> 00:50:58,972
Let's go and eat together.

789
00:51:01,641 --> 00:51:02,893
Do you like Dongbaek?

790
00:51:05,103 --> 00:51:06,188
She's a single mother.

791
00:51:11,193 --> 00:51:14,571
Who are you to ask me that kind of stuff?

792
00:51:15,572 --> 00:51:17,783
I'm asking because I deserve to know.

793
00:51:26,958 --> 00:51:27,959
Is it because

794
00:51:29,002 --> 00:51:30,003
you're Pil-gu's dad?

795
00:51:33,256 --> 00:51:35,258
Is that why you think you deserve to know?

796
00:51:36,051 --> 00:51:36,968
What's your deal?

797
00:51:37,177 --> 00:51:39,930
Do you think you look cool
because you like a pitiful woman?

798
00:51:41,598 --> 00:51:44,810
Don't sway her. Don't pity her, okay?

799
00:51:45,477 --> 00:51:46,520
Mr. Kang.

800
00:51:47,646 --> 00:51:50,273
Do you start liking someone out of pity?

801
00:51:51,191 --> 00:51:53,151
-What?
-You really are

802
00:51:54,027 --> 00:51:54,861
a stupid man.

803
00:51:56,696 --> 00:51:57,697
Don't you know

804
00:51:58,448 --> 00:52:00,367
how attractive Dongbaek is?

805
00:52:05,205 --> 00:52:07,749
You let her go
so you could have everything.

806
00:52:08,208 --> 00:52:09,209
But

807
00:52:10,585 --> 00:52:12,462
I can sacrifice everything
for Dongbaek.

808
00:52:14,965 --> 00:52:16,716
That's how great she is.

809
00:52:17,759 --> 00:52:20,303
You already know that.
That's why you're being so clingy.

810
00:52:20,387 --> 00:52:22,848
Yes, I know.
That's exactly why I'm being so clingy.

811
00:52:22,931 --> 00:52:25,016
I'm going to fix things now that I know.

812
00:52:25,767 --> 00:52:27,519
Now that I found out how she's living,

813
00:52:28,228 --> 00:52:29,396
I can't just ignore her.

814
00:52:33,400 --> 00:52:34,609
What's about her life?

815
00:52:36,278 --> 00:52:38,155
You're the most pitiful person here.

816
00:52:40,031 --> 00:52:41,992
You already lost your chance
with Dongbaek.

817
00:52:42,492 --> 00:52:43,994
She's no longer yours.

818
00:52:44,494 --> 00:52:45,579
And Pil-gu

819
00:52:47,789 --> 00:52:49,082
isn't your son, either.

820
00:52:55,672 --> 00:52:58,425
Hey, you have no right to tell me
that he isn't my son.

821
00:52:58,508 --> 00:53:01,511
The next time you grab me,
be prepared to break a shoulder.

822
00:53:03,847 --> 00:53:05,098
Look at how vulgar you are.

823
00:53:06,349 --> 00:53:07,559
I'm really simple-minded.

824
00:53:08,602 --> 00:53:11,938
You're a great dad to your daughter,
a famous athlete, and you shoot ads.

825
00:53:13,023 --> 00:53:14,482
You're just looking back

826
00:53:14,566 --> 00:53:16,484
and reminiscing the past
in your free time.

827
00:53:17,611 --> 00:53:20,238
But I'm going to put
everything on the line for Dongbaek.

828
00:53:21,781 --> 00:53:22,824
So

829
00:53:23,867 --> 00:53:25,285
stop coming to Ongsan.

830
00:53:26,661 --> 00:53:28,622
Or I'll beat the shit out of you.

831
00:53:38,131 --> 00:53:39,257
He's just like me

832
00:53:40,342 --> 00:53:42,385
back when I was 25 years old.

833
00:53:49,768 --> 00:53:52,854
What did you guys talk about?

834
00:53:54,189 --> 00:53:55,398
Nothing much.

835
00:53:56,274 --> 00:53:58,109
We just had some noodles together.

836
00:54:01,238 --> 00:54:04,157
Dongbaek, try some of this peanut bread.

837
00:54:04,866 --> 00:54:07,452
Everyone has their own social media page.

838
00:54:08,745 --> 00:54:09,913
What?

839
00:54:11,248 --> 00:54:14,542
Everyone has something in the past
that they want to hide

840
00:54:14,626 --> 00:54:16,544
or a small secret of their own.

841
00:54:17,671 --> 00:54:19,589
People all manage to keep things a secret.

842
00:54:19,673 --> 00:54:22,676
But why does my past
always get revealed like this?

843
00:54:24,761 --> 00:54:27,055
You didn't have to meet Pil-gu's dad

844
00:54:27,138 --> 00:54:29,599
and eat noodles with him.

845
00:54:34,020 --> 00:54:35,021
Dongbaek.

846
00:54:36,606 --> 00:54:39,025
The past is just the past.

847
00:54:39,859 --> 00:54:42,404
It holds no power whatsoever.

848
00:54:44,406 --> 00:54:46,741
You say that,
but guys are all pretty much the same.

849
00:54:48,410 --> 00:54:49,452
They're all similar.

850
00:54:52,914 --> 00:54:55,875
Try this peanut bread.

851
00:54:57,752 --> 00:55:00,213
You act like it doesn't bother you,
but men are men.

852
00:55:01,339 --> 00:55:02,882
Who wouldn't be bothered by this?

853
00:55:10,473 --> 00:55:11,433
Dongbaek.

854
00:55:13,768 --> 00:55:15,228
How many guys have you dated?

855
00:55:19,441 --> 00:55:22,819
Kang Jong-ryeol isn't
the only guy in this world.

856
00:55:24,112 --> 00:55:25,280
I'm not like him.

857
00:55:25,864 --> 00:55:27,240
You said you want to see me.

858
00:55:28,491 --> 00:55:29,951
If you think I'm no different,

859
00:55:31,161 --> 00:55:32,579
why would you bother seeing me?

860
00:55:34,664 --> 00:55:36,082
That's not what I meant.

861
00:55:36,541 --> 00:55:37,876
You never tried with me.

862
00:55:38,877 --> 00:55:39,878
Try what?

863
00:55:42,130 --> 00:55:43,089
Dongbaek.

864
00:55:44,007 --> 00:55:45,884
If we actually start a relationship,

865
00:55:47,385 --> 00:55:48,428
I promise...

866
00:55:49,346 --> 00:55:50,347
I promise that...

867
00:55:50,889 --> 00:55:51,765
Gosh.

868
00:55:52,849 --> 00:55:54,142
It'll be out of this world.

869
00:55:55,352 --> 00:56:00,231
You'll be so happy every day
that you'll totally lose it.

870
00:56:06,571 --> 00:56:09,449
So don't compare me to a lousy punk
and say I'm similar to him

871
00:56:09,532 --> 00:56:11,743
when you don't even know
anything about me.

872
00:56:12,952 --> 00:56:15,497
I came to see you at 5 a.m.
because I missed you so much.

873
00:56:15,872 --> 00:56:19,292
So stop making me get so angry.

874
00:56:27,717 --> 00:56:28,802
You're different.

875
00:56:30,804 --> 00:56:32,722
You're very different, Yong-sik.

876
00:56:36,810 --> 00:56:38,144
That's why I'm so grateful--

877
00:56:38,228 --> 00:56:39,938
Will you stop saying you're grateful?

878
00:56:44,109 --> 00:56:45,777
My heart flutters every day.

879
00:56:53,326 --> 00:56:57,455
I didn't know buying flatfish
was such an exciting thing to do.

880
00:57:06,881 --> 00:57:08,842
Should I hold the peanut bread?

881
00:57:10,385 --> 00:57:11,344
Sure.

882
00:57:18,852 --> 00:57:20,645
I don't want to eat anymore. I'm full.

883
00:57:20,728 --> 00:57:21,896
Oh, okay.

884
00:57:24,899 --> 00:57:28,570
Then let me tell you something
about my past as well.

885
00:57:30,822 --> 00:57:32,449
My first love...

886
00:57:33,491 --> 00:57:35,118
My gosh.

887
00:57:36,286 --> 00:57:39,789
It was Seung-yeop's older sister.

888
00:57:42,125 --> 00:57:44,961
We always spent time playing together

889
00:57:45,044 --> 00:57:47,464
in the same neighborhood.

890
00:57:49,048 --> 00:57:51,593
So you guys actually dated each other?

891
00:57:52,594 --> 00:57:53,553
Yes.

892
00:57:55,513 --> 00:57:58,766
But she dumped me

893
00:57:59,350 --> 00:58:01,853
as soon as she went to middle school.

894
00:58:02,145 --> 00:58:06,149
And as she dumped me,
she wrote me a letter

895
00:58:06,774 --> 00:58:09,569
saying she'll beat me up
if I told Seung-yeop that we dated.

896
00:58:10,195 --> 00:58:13,531
So I still haven't told him about it.

897
00:58:14,240 --> 00:58:17,619
I also have a list of exes
in this neighborhood, you know.

898
00:58:19,496 --> 00:58:20,580
I'm serious.

899
00:58:23,416 --> 00:58:26,252
But here's the real secret.

900
00:58:27,337 --> 00:58:29,422
I still don't know

901
00:58:30,381 --> 00:58:33,760
why she dumped me.

902
00:58:34,761 --> 00:58:35,887
My gosh, seriously.

903
00:58:37,388 --> 00:58:39,933
Women are so difficult to understand.

904
00:58:42,519 --> 00:58:46,397
But you're especially more difficult

905
00:58:47,232 --> 00:58:48,900
because I like you so much.

906
00:58:50,777 --> 00:58:51,861
On top of that,

907
00:58:53,780 --> 00:58:55,323
you sometimes get smaller.

908
00:58:58,785 --> 00:59:01,663
No, let me rephrase that.

909
00:59:02,288 --> 00:59:06,709
I'm just saying there are times

910
00:59:06,793 --> 00:59:09,128
when you seem to shrink and wither.

911
00:59:10,838 --> 00:59:15,552
Whenever you're like that,
I don't know what to do to console you

912
00:59:15,635 --> 00:59:18,680
other than buy you sweet snacks like this.
It's really difficult.

913
00:59:20,265 --> 00:59:22,100
And you'll only think

914
00:59:23,309 --> 00:59:26,896
I'm being too chatty
if I talk too much, right?

915
00:59:28,565 --> 00:59:30,775
I like it when you're chatty.

916
00:59:31,359 --> 00:59:33,194
You're an easy guy.

917
00:59:34,696 --> 00:59:35,905
No, I'm quite difficult.

918
00:59:38,616 --> 00:59:41,578
My life's already filled with hardships.

919
00:59:41,661 --> 00:59:45,206
So why can't you just be easy for me?

920
00:59:49,002 --> 00:59:49,836
Okay.

921
00:59:51,129 --> 00:59:52,630
-It's hot, isn't it?
-Yes.

922
00:59:59,220 --> 01:00:03,516
I personally think
that the most underrated hero

923
01:00:03,600 --> 01:00:05,935
is the genie in Aladdin.

924
01:00:06,102 --> 01:00:09,188
If you think about it,
he has no limits to his power.

925
01:00:09,272 --> 01:00:13,234
But he keeps limiting
the number of wishes he can grant.

926
01:00:13,318 --> 01:00:15,445
That made him seem really cheap.

927
01:00:15,570 --> 01:00:17,572
And that's why he can't join the Avengers.

928
01:00:18,740 --> 01:00:20,950
But why are you suddenly
talking about the genie?

929
01:00:21,784 --> 01:00:24,954
You seem to say
whatever that comes to your mind.

930
01:00:30,877 --> 01:00:31,711
Dongbaek.

931
01:00:35,048 --> 01:00:38,718
I'm going to be limitless
when it comes to you.

932
01:00:40,136 --> 01:00:41,596
A hundred wishes in a day? Sure.

933
01:00:41,971 --> 01:00:43,431
If you want 1,000, that's fine.

934
01:00:44,641 --> 01:00:48,561
I'm going to become
the easiest person on Earth

935
01:00:49,854 --> 01:00:51,230
just for you.

936
01:00:56,361 --> 01:00:59,656
You know, the genie is also called
the fairy of the lamp.

937
01:01:01,491 --> 01:01:02,533
What?

938
01:01:03,868 --> 01:01:06,663
Hwang Yong-sik, the fairy. It suits you.

939
01:01:12,710 --> 01:01:13,586
My gosh.

940
01:01:15,755 --> 01:01:17,256
This place is so dark

941
01:01:17,340 --> 01:01:20,176
even during the day
because there are no windows.

942
01:01:20,760 --> 01:01:23,846
Well, I think it's nice and cozy.

943
01:01:25,390 --> 01:01:26,224
Really?

944
01:01:27,517 --> 01:01:29,727
-Yong-sik, just leave it there.
-Okay.

945
01:01:30,436 --> 01:01:31,979
-I'll place it on the table.
-Okay.

946
01:01:39,487 --> 01:01:40,738
What's with the light?

947
01:01:41,406 --> 01:01:42,907
Maybe I need a sensor light--

948
01:01:58,506 --> 01:02:01,426
I TOLD YOU NOT TO BE A JOKE

949
01:02:03,761 --> 01:02:07,181
I'VE BEEN WATCHING YOU EVERY DAY
EVER SINCE THAT DAY

950
01:02:46,220 --> 01:02:47,805
He definitely knows this place.

951
01:02:48,264 --> 01:02:50,057
He even knows
where the camera is.

952
01:02:50,141 --> 01:02:52,101
Pil-gu, should we move?

953
01:02:52,185 --> 01:02:54,562
I just want to raise you somewhere safe.

954
01:02:54,645 --> 01:02:56,189
You should go your own way, Mom.

955
01:02:56,272 --> 01:02:58,024
Figure out
if you have another child.

956
01:02:58,107 --> 01:02:59,734
Once we catch him,

957
01:02:59,817 --> 01:03:02,695
I'm scared he might turn out to be
someone we all know.

958
01:03:02,779 --> 01:03:05,364
Everyone looks nice on the outside.
Don't trust everyone.

959
01:03:05,448 --> 01:03:08,868
No one's curious about the truth.
What they believe becomes the truth.

960
01:03:08,951 --> 01:03:12,163
Do you really think you can take care
of both Dongbaek and Pil-gu?

961
01:03:12,830 --> 01:03:14,624
I keep getting the creeps.

962
01:03:14,707 --> 01:03:16,542
I'm done acting like I'm okay.

963
01:03:18,377 --> 01:03:20,755
Subtitle translation by Liya Choi

